cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is primarily focused on cross-lingual natural language processing tasks, specifically zero-shot cross-lingual transfer parsing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel approach to generate cross-lingual contextualized word embeddings, which involves learning a linear transformation. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses pre-trained BERT models, which are based on neural networks, indicating that it could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a parsing task, which involves analyzing the structure of sentences, suggesting that it could also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
